news.title: Private payrolls rose 42,000 in October, more than expected and countering labor market fears, ADP says
news.summary: Companies added 42,000 jobs for the month, following a decline of 29,000 and topping the estimate for a gain of 22,000.

news.title: Amazon upheaval: With morale shaken, Jassy looks for next big play after mass layoffs
news.summary: Last week, Amazon announced 14,000 layoffs. Amazon CEO Andy Jassy has been overhauling the company's corporate culture in recent years.

news.title: McDonald's earnings miss estimates, but sales are rising in 'challenging environment'
news.summary: McDonald's stock has risen just 3% this year, as investor concerns about the restaurant industry and the broader economy have weighed on shares.

news.title: Democrats win big on election night in key races
news.summary: President Donald Trump said that the reason that Republicans lost big was because he was not on the ballots and because of the federal government shutdown.

news.title: Lyft, United Airlines launch loyalty program months after Delta partnership ends
news.summary: Lyft dissolved its eight-year partnership with Delta Airlines earlier this year. The ride-hailing company also brought its loyalty program to Uber.

news.title: ADP says businesses create 42,000 job in October — but the labor market is still not great
news.summary: Privately run businesses created 42,000 new jobs in October. The increase is the biggest increase in three months. It is a possible sign of stabilization in a weakening U.S. labor market.
